## Issues Encountered

- full WAN outage approximately 3-4 hours after Pi-hole installation
  - date: 06/10/2026
  - symptoms: internet down network-wide, ping 8.8.8.8 timed out from 
    both workstation and Pi via SSH, WAN/DNS red in eero app, ONT lights normal
  - steps taken:
     1. ran dmesg | grep eth0 — ethernet interface stable, no drops logged
     2. pinged 8.8.8.8 from workstation — timed out
     3. pinged 8.8.8.8 from Pi via SSH — timed out
     4. checked ONT — lights normal, ruled out fiber issue
     5. checked eero app — WAN connection showing red (specifically at the DNS level)
 - root cause: ISP-level outage, unrelated to Pi-hole installation
 - fix: self-resolved, ISP restored connection automatically
 - time to resolve: ~10 minutes

